<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1 species; length 25-42 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The dazzling, metallic green 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1812" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Chrysophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysophora chrysochlora" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysochlora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chrysophora chrysochlora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive species and the only member of its genus. The large size, conspicuously rugose elytra, and elongate legs of the male are distinguishing characteristics. Additional characters include the metatibia of the male that is prolonged and acuminate at the apex, the 5th tarsomere with an internal tooth (all legs), the mandibles that are broadly rounded externally, the pronotum with a complete bead, and the mesosternum that is not appreciably produced beyond mesometasternal suture. Research is needed to examine sister-group relationships of this monotypic genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species is distributed in Colombia, Ecuador, and Peru where the Jivaro, Shuar, and Sequoia Indians use the elytra, pronota, legs, or entire body for adornment (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X(2006)60[85:SBIHC]2.0.CO;2" author="Ratcliffe, BC" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B318" refString="Ratcliffe, BC, 2006. Scarab beetles in human culture. The Coleopterists Bulletin 60, Special Issue 5: 85-101. https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X(2006)60[85:SBIHC]2.0.CO;2" title="Scarab beetles in human culture. The Coleopterists Bulletin 60, Special Issue 5: 85 - 101." url="https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X(2006)60[85:SBIHC]2.0.CO;2" year="2006">Ratcliffe 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2317/kent-88-02-186-207.1" author="Ratcliffe, BC" journalOrPublisher="The Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="186 - 207" refId="B321" refString="Ratcliffe, BC, Jameson, ML, Figueroa, L, Cave, RD, Paulsen, MJ, Cano, EB, Beza-Beza, C, Jimenez-Ferbans, L, Reyes-Castillo, R, 2015. Beetles (Coleoptera) of Peru: A survey of families. Scarabaeoidea. The Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 88: 186 - 207, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2317/kent-88-02-186-207.1" title="Beetles (Coleoptera) of Peru: A survey of families. Scarabaeoidea." url="https://doi.org/10.2317/kent-88-02-186-207.1" volume="88" year="2015">Ratcliffe et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Le Tirant, S" journalOrPublisher="Scarabs" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 4" refId="B171" refString="Le Tirant, S, Limoges, R, 2016. Notes on Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini). Scarabs 82: 1 - 4" title="Notes on Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini)." volume="82" year="2016">Le Tirant and Limoges 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The species is primarily found in dry and humid tropical forest between 180-550 m elevation (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" author="Pardo-Locarno, LS" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="80 - 86" refId="B301" refString="Pardo-Locarno, LS, Moron, MA, 2007. Larva and pupa of Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini). The Canadian Entomologist 139: 80 - 86, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" title="Larva and pupa of Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" volume="139" year="2007">
Pardo-Locarno and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morón">Moron</normalizedToken>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), although the species is recorded between 500-1000 m elevation (
<bibRefCitation author="Moron, MA" journalOrPublisher="Sciences Nat, Venette" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B233" refString="Moron, MA, 1990. The Beetles of the World. Volume 10: Rutelini 1. Sciences Nat, Venette" title="The Beetles of the World. Volume 10: Rutelini 1." year="1990">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morón">Moron</normalizedToken>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
). The species is associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Buddleja" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Buddleja" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Buddleja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Buddleja" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Scrophulariaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gynerium sagittatum" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="sagittatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gynerium sagittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Aubl.) Beauvois (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gynerium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
; arrow cane, wild cane) (both 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B286" refString="Ohaus, F, 1934b. Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T.1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199A: 1-172." title="Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T. 1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199 A: 1 - 172." year="1934 b">Ohaus 1934b</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Senna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Senna reticulata" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Senna reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Willd.) H. S. Irwin and Barneby (
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Senna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leguminosae</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Leucaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Leucaena leucocephala" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucocephala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leucaena leucocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lam.) de Wit (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1842" class="Arachnida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Leucaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leguminosae</taxonomicName>
) (both 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" author="Pardo-Locarno, LS" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="80 - 86" refId="B301" refString="Pardo-Locarno, LS, Moron, MA, 2007. Larva and pupa of Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini). The Canadian Entomologist 139: 80 - 86, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" title="Larva and pupa of Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" volume="139" year="2007">
Pardo-Locarno and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morón">Moron</normalizedToken>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). Adults feed on the leaves of 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. sagittatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sagittatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G. sagittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during the day (
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B286" refString="Ohaus, F, 1934b. Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T.1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199A: 1-172." title="Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T. 1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199 A: 1 - 172." year="1934 b">Ohaus 1934b</bibRefCitation>
) from February to May (
<bibRefCitation author="Moron, MA" journalOrPublisher="Sciences Nat, Venette" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B233" refString="Moron, MA, 1990. The Beetles of the World. Volume 10: Rutelini 1. Sciences Nat, Venette" title="The Beetles of the World. Volume 10: Rutelini 1." year="1990">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morón">Moron</normalizedToken>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
), and they fly at twilight or at night (
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Entomologischen Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B286" refString="Ohaus, F, 1934b. Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T.1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199A: 1-172." title="Coleopteralamellicornia, Fam. Scarabaeidae, Subfam. Rutelinae. T. 1: Tribus Rutelini. Genera Insectorum Fasc. 199 A: 1 - 172." year="1934 b">Ohaus 1934b</bibRefCitation>
). Larvae and pupae are described and share several characters with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1819" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pelidnota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pelidnota" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pelidnota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae and pupae (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" author="Pardo-Locarno, LS" journalOrPublisher="The Canadian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="80 - 86" refId="B301" refString="Pardo-Locarno, LS, Moron, MA, 2007. Larva and pupa of Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini). The Canadian Entomologist 139: 80 - 86, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" title="Larva and pupa of Chrysophora chrysochlora (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Rutelinae: Rutelini)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/n06-002" volume="139" year="2007">
Pardo-Locarno and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morón">Moron</normalizedToken>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
